    "code": "```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <!-- Basic document metadata -->\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Simple Calculator</title>\n\n    <!-- Link to the stylesheet that will style the calculator -->\n    <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"styles.css\">\n</head>\n<body>\n\n    <!-- --------------------------------------------------------------\n         Calculator root element \u2013 all UI lives inside this container.\n         -------------------------------------------------------------- -->\n    <div id=\"calculator\">\n\n        <!-- Display area \u2013 shows the current expression and the result -->\n        <div id=\"display\" class=\"display\"></div>\n\n        <!-- ----------------------------------------------------------\n             Buttons container \u2013 a grid of all calculator keys.\n             ------------------------------------------------------- -->\n        <div class=\"buttons\">\n\n            <!-- Row 1 -->\n            <button data-type=\"clear\"   data-value=\"C\">C</button>\n            <button data-type=\"delete\"  data-value=\"\u2190\">&larr;</button>\n            <button data-type=\"operator\" data-value=\"/\">&#247;</button>\n            <button data-type=\"operator\" data-value=\"*\">&#215;</button>\n\n            <!-- Row 2 -->\n            <button data-type=\"digit\"    data-value=\"7\">7</button>\n            <button data-type=\"digit\"    data-value=\"8\">8</button>\n            <button data-type=\"digit\"    data-value=\"9\">9</button>\n            <button data-type=\"operator\" data-value=\"-\">&#8722;</button>\n\n            <!-- Row 3 -->\n            <button data-type=\"digit\"    data-value=\"4\">4</button>\n            <button data-type=\"digit\"    data-value=\"5\">5</button>\n            <button data-type=\"digit\"    data-value=\"6\">6</button>\n            <button data-type=\"operator\" data-value=\"+\">+</button>\n\n            <!-- Row 4 -->\n            <button data-type=\"digit\"    data-value=\"1\">1</button>\n            <button data-type=\"digit\"    data-value=\"2\">2</button>\n            <button data-type=\"digit\"    data-value=\"3\">3</button>\n            <button data-type=\"equals\"  data-value=\"=\">=</button>\n\n            <!-- Row 5 -->\n            <button data-type=\"digit\"    data-value=\"0\" class=\"zero\">0</button>\n            <button data-type=\"decimal\"  data-value=\".\">.</button>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Load the JavaScript that will handle the calculator logic -->\n    <script src=\"app.js\"></script>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n**Explanation of the markup**\n\n* **`<div id=\"calculator\">`** \u2013 the main wrapper; CSS will size and position it.\n* **`<div id=\"display\" class=\"display\"></div>`** \u2013 empty element that JavaScript updates with the current input / result.\n* **Buttons**\n  * Every button receives a `data-type` attribute that tells the script what kind of key it is (`digit`, `operator`, `clear`, `delete`, `decimal`, `equals`).\n  * `data-value` holds the actual character/symbol that should be processed.\n  * The visual label of the button is the same character (or a HTML entity for nicer symbols).\n  * The `class=\"zero\"` on the \u201c0\u201d button is optional \u2013 it can be used by CSS to make the zero button span two columns if desired.\n\nThe file links to **`styles.css`** for styling and **`app.js`** for the interactive behavior, satisfying the requirements of the task."
